OL,3,CJersey government staff costs go up by
OL,4,C#73 million
OL,6,FAt a scrutiny hearing, Chief Minister
OL,7,FLyndon Farnham suggested there could
OL,8,Fbe some job cutting with a focus on
OL,9,Fthe Cabinet Office, communications and
OL,10,Fsome management positions.
OL,12,FTreasury Minister Deputy Elaine Millar
OL,13,Fsays she is not keen on cutting
OL,14,Ffrontline jobs, but there could be
OL,15,Fsavings in other departments.
OL,17,FShe told me: "I don't think they will
OL,18,Fbe significant but I would expect they
OL,19,Fwere more likely to be done through
OL,20,Fvacancy management rather than large-
OL,21,Fscale redundancy.
